MODULE.name: AUDPROC_MODULE_ID_AUDIOSPHERE
MODULE.description:
ID of the Audiosphere module.
This module supports the#[ #] following parameter IDs:
- #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_ENABLE - #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_STRENGTH - #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_CONFIG_MODE -#[ #] #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILT_COEFFS_STEREO_INPUT - #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILT_COEFFS_MULTICHANNEL_INPUT -#[ #] #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILTER_DESIGN_STEREO_INPUT - #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILTER_DESIGN_MULTICHANNEL_INPUT -#[ #] #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_OPERATING_INPUT_MEDIA_INFO - #AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_ENABLE All parameter IDs are device independent.

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_ENABLE
PARAMETER.description: ID of the AudioSphere Enable parameter used by#[ #] AUDPROC_MODULE_ID_AUDIOSPHERE.\nPayload of the AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_ENABLE parameter used by the AudioSphere module.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: enable_flag
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies whether the AudioSphere module is enabled.

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_STRENGTH
PARAMETER.description: ID of the AudioSphere Strength parameter used by#[ #] #AUDPROC_MODULE_ID_AUDIOSPHERE.\nPayload of the AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_STRENGTH parameter used by the AudioSphere module.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: strength
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the effects of the audiosphere.\n 0 -- No effects \n 1000 -- Maximum effects

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_CONFIG_MODE
PARAMETER.description: ID of the AudioSphere Configuration mode parameter#[ #] used by #AUDPROC_MODULE_ID_AUDIOSPHERE.\n Payload of the AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_CONFIG_MODE parameter used by the AudioSphere module.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: version
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the version information of this parameter.\n (currently, only 0 is supported)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: config_mode
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the mode of operation for the AudioSphere.

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILT_COEFFS_STEREO_INPUT
PARAMETER.description: Payload of the#[ #] AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILT_COEFFS parameter used by the AudioSphere module.\n Following this structure is a payload that is a sequence of#[ #] int32 Imaginary coeffs -- 2-D array[num_filters][fft_size/2+1]. The total number of cint2x32 coefficients is defined by#[ #] (num_filters*(fft_size/2+1)). In this case, the total number is 2052, where num_filters is 4 and fft_size is 1024.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: version
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the version information of this parameter.(currently, only 0 is supported)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: sample_rate
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the sample rate of the filter coefficients.(48000 Hz - AudioSphere-supported sample rate)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: fft_size
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the length of FFT.

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILT_COEFFS_MULTICHANNEL_INPUT
PARAMETER.description: Payload of the#[ #] AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILT_COEFFS parameter used by the AudioSphere module.\n Following this structure is a payload that is a sequence of#[ #] int32 Imaginary coeffs -- 2-D array[num_filters][fft_size/2+1]. The total number of cint2x32 coefficients is defined by#[ #] (num_filters*(fft_size/2+1)). In this case, the total number is 2052, where num_filters is 4 and fft_size is 1024.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: version
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the version information of this parameter.(currently, only 0 is supported)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: sample_rate
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the sample rate of the filter coefficients.(48000 Hz - AudioSphere-supported sample rate)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: fft_size
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the length of FFT.

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILTER_DESIGN_STEREO_INPUT
PARAMETER.description: Payload of the#[ #] AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILTER_DESIGN parameter used by the AudioSphere module.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: version
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the version information of this parameter.(currently, only 0 is supported)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: speaker_distance
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the distance (in millimeters) between speakers on the handset (in mm). This value is used for designing the filter#[ #] coefficients.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: head_distance
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the distance (in millimeters) between center of the head and the device. This value is used for designing the filter#[ #] coefficients.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: back_angle
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the angle of the rear virtual speakers. This value is used for designing the filter coefficients.\n Any positive value in#[ #] degrees (0 is the forward direction)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: front_angle
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the angle of the front virtual speakers. This value is used for designing the filter coefficients.\nAny positive value in#[ #] degrees (0 is the forward direction)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: max_freq_gain
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the maximum frequency gain (in decibels) provided by the corresponding filter coefficients.\nAny value in dB

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILTER_DESIGN_MULTICHANNEL_INPUT
PARAMETER.description: Payload of the#[ #] AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_FILTER_DESIGN parameter used by the AudioSphere module.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: version

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: speaker_distance
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the distance (in millimeters) between speakers on the handset (in mm). This value is used for designing the filter#[ #] coefficients.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: head_distance
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the distance (in millimeters) between center of the head and the device. This value is used for designing the filter#[ #] coefficients.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: back_angle
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the angle of the rear virtual speakers. This value is used for designing the filter coefficients.\n Any positive value in#[ #] degrees (0 is the forward direction)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: front_angle
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the angle of the front virtual speakers. This value is used for designing the filter coefficients.\nAny positive value in#[ #] degrees (0 is the forward direction)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: max_freq_gain

PARAMETER.name: AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_OPERATING_INPUT_MEDIA_INFO
PARAMETER.description: Payload of the#[ #] AUDPROC_PARAM_ID_AUDIOSPHERE_OPERATING_INPUT_MEDIA_INFO parameter used by the AudioSphere module.

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: version
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Specifies the version information of this parameter.(currently, only 0 is supported)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: num_input_channel
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Number of input channels to the AudioSphere module.\n(Any other value -- Reserved for future use @tablebulletend)

RANGE.name: No valid media format is received (Default)

CONFIG_ELEMENT.name: sample_rate
CONFIG_ELEMENT.description: Sample rate at which the AudioSphere module is operating.\n (currently, only 48000 Hz is supported)

RANGE.name: No valid media format is received (Default)
